# .trivyignore — Trivy misconfiguration suppression rules
#
# These suppressions apply to Trivy's static (pre-render) analysis of Helm
# chart template files. Trivy reads raw Go template expressions such as
#   {{ include "nexus-hems.imageRef" (dict ...) | quote }}
# and cannot resolve them to actual image strings without executing Helm.
# The actual image validation is enforced at `helm template` render time by
# the `nexus-hems.assertTrustedImageRepository` helper in _helpers.tpl, which
# calls `fail()` if the repository does not start with a prefix from
# `.Values.image.trustedRegistries` (defaults to ["ghcr.io/qnbs/"]).
#
# Rule: KSV034 — Restrict container images to only those from approved registries
# Affected files: Helm deployment templates (static template text, not rendered output)

KSV034
